<HEADLINE> Iranian Diplomats Recalled From Pakistan for </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TEHRAN, October 3 (Xinhua) -- Iranian Foreign Minister Kamal
Kharrazi said here Saturday that the number of Iranian diplomats
in Pakistan was reduced due to the insecure state in that country.
</P>
<P>
According to the evening daily Kayhan, Kharrazi termed the
recall of a group of Iranian diplomats as "a security issue."
</P>
<P>
"There have been many terrorist acts in Pakistan during recent
months and a number of Iranians serving in Pakistan were
martyred," he said after returning from a session of the United
Nations General Assembly in New York.
</P>
<P>
Kharrazi said that it is normal for a country to recall its
diplomats who were not in safe, but under danger.
</P>
<P>
The Iranian diplomats will return to Pakistan after the
improvement of security in that country, Kharrazi added.
</P>
<P>
Iran recalled some 60 diplomats and their families from
Islamabad following a series of terrorist assassination in
Pakistan and the killing of nine Iranian diplomats and reporter
in Afghanistan.
</P>
<P>
The move came after Tehran-Islamabad ties were challenged by
the killing of Iranian diplomats by the Pakistan-supported Afghan
Taliban forces.
</P>
<P>
However, the Iranian Foreign Ministry spokesman Mahmoud
Mohammadi said on Thursday that the return of Iranian diplomats
from Pakistan does not mean any change in the level of diplomatic
relations between the two countries. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
