<HEADLINE> Tyson Ready to Explode under Pressure </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, October 3 (Xinhua) -- Mike Tyson says he's bitter
and defensive, and a threat to explode. The former heavyweight
champion made the comments in an interview in this month's
Playboy magazine.
</P>
<P>
"I know I'm going to blow one day," Tyson was quoted as saying
in the profanity-laced interview, which was conducted in July
before his appearance before the New Jersey Athletic Commission.
</P>
<P>
He described himself as a "hateful individual."
</P>
<P>
"My life is doomed the way it is, I have no future," Tyson
said. "I feel bad about my outlook, how I feel about people and
society, and that I'll never be part of society the way I
should."  
</P>
</TEXT>
