<HEADLINE> Egypt to Cooperate With Jordan in Treating </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
AMMAN, October 3 (Xinhua) -- Egypt has said it accepts any
decision by Jordan to handle the Egyptians working in the kingdom
in its drive to curb employment of foreigners.
</P>
<P>
Egypt is also convicted that any measure by the Jordanian
government on foreign workers will be aimed at protecting them and
maintaining their rights, Egyptian Ambassador to Amman Jamo Riyad
said Saturday after a meeting with Jordanian Minister of Labor
Mohammad Mehdi Farhan.
</P>
<P>
During the meeting, Farhan discussed with Riyad various issues
related to the ongoing campaign to strictly regulate the foreign
labor market and create jobs for locals.
</P>
<P>
Hundreds of Asian workers have been detained during the
campaign since Wednesday. Those without work permits will be
prosecuted or expelled. The government has begun preparations to
deal with the Arab workers in the same way.
</P>
<P>
There are about 300,000 to 500,000 guest workers now live in
Jordan, of whom only 40 percent hold valid work permits, according
to official figures.
</P>
<P>
Some 90 percent out of the total guest workers in Jordan are
Egyptians. Last year, the government ordered the illegal Egyptian
workers either to leave the kingdom or to apply for work
permits. The deadline for such a decision was extended for three
times, but most of the Egyptians refused to cooperate and the
problem still remained unsolved. 
</P>
</TEXT>
