<TEXT>
<P>
TEHRAN, October 3 (Xinhua) -- Iran on Saturday called on the
Turkish government to exercise self-restraint in its war of words
with Syria.
</P>
<P>
"Any tension between the Islamic states will only serve to
strengthen the aggressive stand of the Zionist regime (Israel)
and will have negative impact on the security of the Middle East
and the Palestinian nation," Foreign Ministry spokesman Mahmoud
Mohammadi Mohammadi said.
</P>
