state of war" existed between Ankara and Damascus as Turkey blamed
Syria for helping outlawed Kurdish groups to fight against the
Turkish government.
</P>
<P>
Syria rejected Turkey's accusation, but criticized Ankara for
provoking problems with its neighbors.
</P>
<P>
Turkey and Syria are required to settle their dispute
through peaceful negotiations, Mohammadi said, adding that Israel
has embarked on aggressive policies, attempting to create division
between the Muslim and Arab states.
</P>
<P>
He also urged Turkey to revise its close relations with Israel
in a bid to reinforce Islamic solidarity and cooperation between
the Islamic states. 
