<HEADLINE> Iranian Army's New Chief of Staff Appointed </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TEHRAN, October 3 (Xinhua) -- The newly-appointed commander of
the Iranian army Major General Ali Shahbazi has appointed Mostafa
Torabipour to replace him as the army's chief of staff, the
evening daily Kayhan reported on Saturday.
</P>
<P>
The appointment was announced at the ceremony to introduce
Shahbazi as the army's commander. Shahbazi was appointed on
Wednesday by Ayatollah Ali Khamenei, the supreme leader and
command-in-chief of the country's armed forces.
</P>
<P>
During the ceremony, Major General Naser Arasteh was also
introduced as the first deputy commander of the army and Major
General Mehdi Montazeri as head of the army's information
protection body.
</P>
<P>
It was the first time for the Iranian army to have a commander
since the Islamic Revolution in 1979.
</P>
<P>
The Iranian army is a part of the armed forces, which also
include the Islamic Revolutionary Guards Corps (IRGC) and the
security forces (or armed police). Both the army and the IRGC
have their own naval, ground and air forces.
</P>
<P>
The IRGC has been commanded by its commander since its
establishment in 1979, but the army was headed only by the chief
of staff during the past two decades.
</P>
<P>
Chief of Staff of Iranian Armed Forces Major General Hassan
Firuzabadi said at the ceremony that the forthcoming Zoulfaqar-2
maneuvers necessitated the formation of the new post of the army
commander.
</P>
<P>
He said that Shahbazi would be in charge of the operations of
the army's naval, ground and air forces.
</P>
<P>
Following the tension between Iran and the Afghan Taliban
forces, the Iranian army announced to launch its biggest maneuvers
along the eastern border with Afghanistan with the participation
of 200,000 troops.
</P>
<P>
The army started the preliminary military exercises on
Wednesday, but the date for the main stage of the maneuver has not
been announced so far. 
</P>
</TEXT>
