<HEADLINE> Arab Singers Gather in Beirut for Arab Unity </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIRUT, October 3 (Xinhua) -- Singers from seven Arab
countries got together here Saturday night to sing a common song
urging Arab unity in the fight against Israel.
</P>
<P>
Twenty-three leading singers in these countries accompanied by
Lebanon's celebrities performed different verses of the song "The
Arab Dream" in the open-air show held at Martyrs' Square in
Beirut's central district.
</P>
<P>
More than 10,000 Lebanese, including the country's politicians,
writers, poets, composers and actors, attended the show entitled
"Voice of One million Arabs."
</P>
<P>
"Arab nations suffer from similar hardships to other countries
but Israel is one evil we don't share with the rest of the world,"
said the show's producer Ahmad Aryan.
</P>
<P>
"The song will bring 1 million Arabs together, whether they
attend the show or watch it on television," he told reporters.
</P>
<P>
A video of the song, which depicts distressing scenes of death
and destruction caused by Israel's assaults on several Arab
countries, was also shown at the event which was sponsored by
Lebanese Prime Minister Rafik Hariri.
</P>
<P>
"I want to show the world how Israel has been and still is a
major source of misery for Arabs by using motion pictures, a
language everyone understands," said Aryan, also the director and
mastermind behind the video version.
</P>
<P>
Since the beginning of August, the video has been broadcast
regularly on Arab satellite and local television stations.
</P>
<P>
Aryan also plans to broadcast his video on the United
States and European channels. 
</P>
</TEXT>
