<HEADLINE> Mubarak Ends Surprise Visit to Saudi Arabia </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KUWAIT CITY, October 3 (Xinhua) -- Egyptian President Hosni
Mubarak left Riyadh Saturday, ending a surprise visit after
holding talks with Saudi King Fahd Ibn Abdul-Aziz on the latest
Middle East peace developments and bilateral relations.
</P>
<P>
The Kuwait News Agency (Kuna) quoted diplomatic sources in
Riyadh as saying that Mubarak arrived earlier in the day for an
undeclared short visit.
</P>
<P>
The visit focused on the recent Middle East peace developments
following the recent Washington meeting between Palestinian and
Israeli leaders, the sources added.
</P>
<P>
Mubarak and Fahd were also believed to have discussed the
recent escalating of tension between Syria and Turkey and other
Islamic issues such as the Kosovo and the Iran-Afghanistan crisis.
</P>
<P>
Turkish Prime Minister Mesut Yilmaz said earlier Saturday that
Turkish troops were awaiting orders to launch a military offensive
against Syria, which Yilmaz accused of supporting Kurdish rebels
against Turkey.
</P>
<P>
Egyptian Foreign Minister Amr Moussa said Saturday that his
country was trying hard to defuse the tension between Turkey and
Syria.
</P>
<P>
Moussa said that Mubarak earlier had telephone conversation
with his Syria counterpart Hafez al-Assad and was due to speak to
Turkish President Suleyman Demirel. 
</P>
