<HEADLINE> Jordan Calls for Dialog Between Turkey, Syria </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
AMMAN, October 3 (Xinhua) -- Jordan on Saturday called on
Turkey and Syria to conduct constructive dialog to contain the
crisis between them and settle their disputes.
</P>
<P>
A peaceful settlement is in the interests of the two countries
and will contribute to the stability and security of the Middle
East, Jordanian Minister of Information Nasir Judeh told reporters
after a regular cabinet session.
</P>
<P>
"The region's higher interests do not afford new escalation
(of tension) that leads to new crisis," he said.
</P>
<P>
Jordan will employ its relations with all the concerned parties
to mediate between Syria and Turkey, he added, noting Jordan
maintains good relations with both countries.
</P>
<P>
Turkey's top military officials have said their country is in a
state of undeclared war with Syria due to Damascus' alleged
support for Kurdish rebels against Turkey.
</P>
<P>
Rejecting Turkey's accusation, Syria said a Turkish-Israeli
military alliance is behind the rise of tension between the two
neighboring countries. 
</P>
