<HEADLINE> Middle East Economic Briefs </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CAIRO, October 3 (Xinhua) -- The following are economic briefs
from Middle East countries.
</P>
<P>
CAIRO -- Egypt's Minister of Trade and Supply Ahmed Gowaili
said the value of Egypt's textile exports over the last eight
months totaled 3.1 billion Egyptian pounds (912 million
U.S. dollars), 44 million pounds (13 million dollars) less than
that of the same period last year.
</P>
<P>
According to Saturday's Al-Ahram, Gowaili attributed this to
the dumping cases and the recess of the European markets.
</P>
<P>
Gowaili called for more efforts this year to reach Egypt's
national target of 4 billion pounds (1.12 billion dollars) from
the textile exports.
</P>
<P>
