<HEADLINE> Rios Outlasts Agassi to Win Grand Slam Cup </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BERLIN, October 4 (Xinhua) -- Chile's Marcelo Rios outlasted
American Andre Agassi in a five-set battle to win the Grand Slam
Cup men's final on Sunday in Munich, Germany.
</P>
<P>
World number three player Rios, the highest ranked player of
the tournament, played more calmly to beat Agassi 6-4, 2-6, 7-6
(7-1), 5-7, 6-3 in two hours and 55 minutes.
</P>
<P>
While the American, who is No. 8 in the world, seemed to lose
his elegant returns and powerful baseliners after playing two
five-set matches in two days.
</P>
<P>
Agassi's double-faults gave the victory to Rios and pocketed
650,000 U.S. dollars prize bonus, half of the amount Rios took
after he won the trophy.
</P>
<P>
The 6.7 million U.S. dollars tournament aims to bring all the
four Grand Slam events champions, but three of them did not show
up for unknown reasons. 
</P>
</TEXT>
