<HEADLINE> Greece Calls for Political Solution to Kosovo Crisis </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ATHENS, October 4 (Xinhua) -- Greece on Sunday urged leaders of
the Yugoslav federation and ethnic Albanians in its province of
Kosovo to begin talks immediately.
</P>
<P>
The purpose of the talks, as stated by Defense Minister Akis
Tsohatzopoulos in the northern Greek city of Thessaloniki, is to
avert a possible military intervention by NATO.
</P>
<P>
