<HEADLINE> Kuwaiti Navy to Conduct Live Ammunition Drills </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KUWAIT CITY, October 4 (Xinhua) -- Kuwaiti navy will conduct
exercises with live ammunition near Jazirat Kubbar Island in the
Gulf on October 10-13, the Kuwaiti Army said in a statement Sunday.
</P>
<P>
According to the official news agency Kuna, the statement
warned against approaching the sea block, about 50 kilometers
southeast of the capital, between 8 a.m. and 3 p.m. (0500-1200
GMT) during the days of maneuvers.
</P>
<P>
But Kuna failed to give any details as to the scale and purpose
of the drills. Kuwait used to hold joint military exercises over
the past years with the U.S., aiming at improving its soldiers'
combat skills and readiness.
</P>
<P>
The small Gulf country entered a defense cooperation agreement
with the U.S. in 1991 after invading Iraqi troops were driven out
of its territory by the U.S.-led allied forces in the Gulf War.
</P>
<P>
Since then, dozens of various joint military exercises have
been carried out by the two sides in the Kuwaiti territory as well
as in the Gulf. 
