<HEADLINE> Clashes in Somalia Kills 3 After 6 Die in Road </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MOGADISHU, October 4 (Xinhua) -- Two more people died Sunday
in a hospital in Mogadishu after sustaining wounds when the heavy
duty truck they were in overturned near Warmahan Village, 60 km
south of the Somali capital.
</P>
<P>
According to eyewitnesses, four were dead on the spot, and 13
others were wounded Saturday night when the accident happened.
</P>
<P>
The reason for the tragic accident is not known. However,
survivors of the accident told reporters that the truck was
traveling at a high speed on the dark road between Ballidogle
airport and Mogadishu when the front tires of the vehicle fell in
a small hole in the middle of the road.
</P>
<P>
One of the front tires subsequently exploded making the
vehicle loose control and direction before turning over.
</P>
<P>
The trouble did not end there as three battle wagons and more
than 35 armed militiamen escorting the overturned vehicle and
another truck transporting goods from Ballidogle to Mogadishu
engaged in a serious armed confrontation with militiamen manning
a roadblock at the former custodian police headquarters near K-7
strong point Sunday at about 14:00 hours local time.
</P>
<P>
Militiamen escorting the trucks blamed the militiamen of Osman
Ali Atto for starting the shooting in their attempt to obtain the
extortion money by force.
</P>
<P>
The ensued clashes have left at least three people dead and
more than five others wounded although the three battle wagons
have managed to go through the checkpoint forcefully.
</P>
<P>
Nearly 70 illegal roadblocks are set up along the road between
Mogadishu and Ballidogle airport demanding the drivers to pay
extortion money. 
</P>
</TEXT>
