<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Agricultural Growth Ensured </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, October 4 (Xinhua) -- China is expecting to ensure the
sustained development of agriculture, which is seen as the
prerequisite for the country's overall economic growth, social
stability and low inflation.
</P>
<P>
The central government will soon implement a policy that
requires every unit area of farmland used for non-agricultural
purposes be compensated for by one unit area of land of the same
size to be reclaimed by the user.
</P>
<P>
Protection of farmland is a key measure taken by the Chinese
government to ensure the future of agriculture, said Long Bing, an
official with the State Land Administration.
</P>
<P>
China is the third largest country in the world, but its
per-capita share of cultivated land stands at merely 0.1 hectare,
one-third of the world average. And for years, large area of
cultivated land have been used for industrial and urban
development.
</P>
<P>
Starting form the mid-1980s, the Chinese government began to
strengthen ways of protecting farmland, 70 percent of which is now
under protection.
</P>
<P>
According to the Ministry of Land and Natural Resources, the
government set a one-year ban in April 1997 on the use of
cultivated land for non-agricultural use. The ban has been
extended and will be effective "until a revised Land
Administration Law now being drafted comes into effect."
</P>
<P>
Funeral and interment practices are being changed to save
land. Farmers traditionally bury their dead in graves close to
their homes, but now this can only be done if the land is
non-agricultural.
</P>
<P>
Local governments are encouraging public cemeteries to be built
in hilly areas.
</P>
<P>
Apart from sustaining the area where crops are grown,
agriculture development also demands improvement of the
yields. Application of science and technology is believed to play
a key role in this regard.
</P>
<P>
In 1997, the technique of the use of plastic film to cover
newly-sown crops boosted national grain production by 220 million
kilograms.
</P>
<P>
Plastic film will cover a total of 530,000 hectares of farmland
this year, 2.8 times the 1997 figure, according to the Ministry of
Agriculture.
</P>
<P>
Another agrotechnique that has achieved success is Chinese
hybrid rice developed by Yuan Longping and his colleagues.
</P>
<P>
By the end of last year, the high-yielding hybrid rice had been
grown on 200 million hectares of land. Its introduction has
boosted rice output by 300 billion kilograms. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
