<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Passenger Arrivals to Macao Rise in August </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MACAO, October 4 (Xinhua) -- Latest figures from the Macao
Census and Statistics Department show that passenger arrivals to
Macao reached 709,592 in August this year, up 30.8 percent from
the same month of 1997.
</P>
<P>
However, the figures also indicate that total passenger
arrivals in the first eight months of the year decreased by 2.6
percent compared with the same period last year.
</P>
<P>
Between January and August, passengers from China's mainland
and Hong Kong accounted for 76.5 percent of the total entering
Macao, an increase of 7.8 percent over last year.
</P>
<P>
In comparison, passengers from the Republic of Korea, Japan,
Southeast Asia and South Asia plunged considerably. The decline is
believed to be a result of the drawn-out financial crisis in the
region. 
</P>
</TEXT>
