<HEADLINE> HK Unveils 1999 Stamps Issuing Program </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, October 4 (Xinhua) -- Hong Kong Postmaster General
Robert Footman announced here Sunday that Hong Kong will issue six
 sets of special stamps in 1999 with one set to commemorate the
50th anniversary of the founding of the People's Republic of China
 (PRC).
</P>
<P>
The 50th anniversary set will comprise four denominations, to
be issued on October 1, the National Day of the PRC.
</P>
<P>
Announcing the stamp issuing program for 1999, Footman said
Hong Kong will issue scratch-off stamps for the first time.
</P>
<P>
"These will be for Chinese Lunar New Year Greetings and should
be of special interest to collectors," Footman said.
</P>
<P>
This set of stamps, to be issued on January 31, 1999, will
comprise four denominations featuring greeting messages of the
Lunar New Year.
</P>
<P>
Special scratch-off ink will be applied on the stamps to cover
the greeting message printed underneath. A mini-pane with 10
different greeting messages for each denomination will also be
released, Footman said.
</P>
<P>
On March 14, a set of stamps comprising four denominations
featuring common activities undertaken by elderly people will be
issued to mark the International Year of Older Persons.
</P>
<P>
Another set of special stamps to be issued next year will
feature Hong Kong Public Road Transport. The four stamps to be
issued on May 23 will depict four kinds of public road
transportation in Hong Kong -- bus, taxi, tram and the airport
express.
</P>
<P>
A set of stamps on tourism will be issued jointly with
Singapore on July 1, Footman said. There will be six stamps
depicting three landmarks of Hong Kong and three landmarks of
Singapore. A souvenir sheet will also be issued.
</P>
<P>
The last set of special stamps will be issued on November 14
featuring Chinese White Dolphin. There will be four stamps
depicting Chinese White Dolphins in action.
</P>
<P>
This set of stamps will form one of the World Wide Fund For
Nature's Conservation Stamp Collection, Footman said. A souvenir
sheet will also be issued, he said.
</P>
<P>
In addition to the six sets of special stamps, there will also
be stamp sheetlets featuring 12 animals of the Lunar New Year
Cycle. A stamp sheetlet depicting a giant panda will be issued to
commemorate the arrival of the giant pandas from the mainland.
</P>
<P>
A stamp sheetlet will be issued to commemorate the opening of
the "China 1999 World Philatelic Exhibition" in Beijing.
</P>
<P>
A new set of definitive stamps depicting Hong Kong sceneries
will be issued on October 18, Footman said. Starting from 1999,
presentation packs will be issued along with all new stamps and
stamp sheetlets issues, he added. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19981004.0079 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1998-10-04 </DATE_TIME>
