<HEADLINE> SriLankan Troops kill at least 6 Tamil Rebels </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
COLOMBO, October 4 (Xinhua) -- At least six Tamil rebels were
killed when Sri Lankan government troops advanced further
northwards Saturday from the newly recaptured Mankulam areas,
according to a military spokesman Sunday.
</P>
<P>
Spokesman Ink Dewage said rebels of the Liberation Tigers of
Tamil Eelam (LTTE) fired mortars at the advancing troops, who then
retaliated "effectively," causing heavy casualties among the
rebels.
</P>
<P>
The troops cleared the rebels' trench line north west of
Mankulam town, and killed several rebels and recovered some
weapons, he said.
</P>
<P>
Early on Sunday at Thandikulam in Vavuniya district, LTTE
rebels exploded three claymore mines against army vehicles,
killing one soldier and one civilian, and injuring two soldiers,
said Dewage.
</P>
<P>
The LTTE rebels have been fighting a war against the Sri Lankan
government since 1983 for a separate state in the north and east
of the island country. 
</P>
