<BODY>
<HEADLINE> 60 Kilograms of Heroin Seized in Turkey </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ANKARA, October 4 (Xinhua) -- A total of 60 kilograms of pure
heroin has been seized in an operation against drug trafficking in
eastern Turkey, the semi-official Anatolia News Agency reported
Sunday.
</P>
<P>
The agency said that acting on tip off, the Turkish police
stopped a tanker on the Van-Ercis highway in eastern province of
Van linking neighboring Iran and found the heroin in packets
planted in the vehicle. However, the agency did not report when
the heroin was confiscated.
</P>
<P>
The driver of the tanker was detained in connection with
the drug incident in the area, said the agency.
</P>
<P>
Turkey is on a transit route of drugs to Europe from the border
areas of Afghanistan and Pakistan. In 1996, Turkish police seized
4.4 tonnes of heroin, which accounted for 40 percent of the
world's total haul. 
</P>
</TEXT>
