<BODY>
<HEADLINE> South Korea Wins Asian Table Tennis Women's Doubles </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TOKYO, October 4 (Xinhua) -- Ryu Ji-Hye/Lee Eun-Sil beat Kim
Moo-Kyo/Park Hae-Jung in an all-Korean women's doubles final at
the Asian table tennis championships in Osaka on Sunday.
</P>
<P>
Ryu and Lee triumphed 21-17, 21-9.
</P>
<P>
Earlier, Ryu and Lee shocked top seeds and defending champions
Li Ju and Wang Nan from China 21-16, 14-21, 21-16 and then dashed
any Chinese hopes by beating Wong Chin and Wong Hui 21-12, 13-21,
21-14 on their way to the final.
</P>
<P>
Park and Kim eliminated the last local hope of Akiko Takeda
and Mayu Kawagoe 19-21, 23-21, 21-17 in the other semi-finals.
</P>
</TEXT>
