<HEADLINE> 21 Kg Heroin Seized at Bangkok Airport </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BANGKOK, October 4 (Xinhua) -- The Thai Customs Department
seized 21 kilograms of heroin from a foreigner at Bangkok's
international airport Saturday, the Bangkok Post reported Sunday.
</P>
<P>
Yenri Suen Onabanjo, 32, traveling on a Malawian passport, was
arrested and charged with drug trafficking as he was about to
board a plane to Addis Ababa, Ethiopia, officials were quoted as
saying.
</P>
<P>
The heroin, which was hidden in radio loudspeakers, is worth up
to 500 million baht (12.5 million U.S. dollars) outside the
country.
</P>
<P>
The suspect is part of an international drug ring allegedly run
by a group of Nigerians, officials said.
</P>
<P>
In the last three months, the Customs Department has
confiscated 80 kilograms of heroin. Its value is as high as 25
billion baht (625 million U.S. dollars) outside the country,
according to the department. 
</P>
</TEXT>
