<HEADLINE> Hurricane Georges Destroys 57,934 Houses in Puerto Rico </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SAN JUAN, October 3 (Xinhua) -- One third of the 169,569 houses
hit by hurricane Georges in Puerto Rico were completely destroyed,
the American Red Cross (ARC) said on Saturday.
</P>
<P>
The eastern region of the island was the hardest hit, with
63,139 houses partially or totally damaged.
</P>
<P>
In the northern region 44,513 homes were affected, while in the
south and west, 44,515 and 17,402 houses respectively suffered
total or partial damage. 
</P>
</TEXT>
