<HEADLINE> China and U.S. to Jointly Develop Medicine </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, October 4 (Xinhua) -- Chinese and U.S. medical experts
are to join hands to test traditional Chinese medicines for
approval by the U.S. Food and Drug Administration (FDA), today's
China Daily reported.
</P>
<P>
The cooperation between the Covance Medicine Development
Services Company from the U.S., and the China Innovation Center
for Life Sciences and major Chinese pharmaceutical companies will
also promote traditional Chinese medicines in the U.S. market,
said Chris Kuebler, chairman and chief executive officer of
Covance, at the recent opening ceremony of the company's new
office in Beijing.
</P>
<P>
In accordance with FDA standards, Covance's Beijing office and
the China Innovation Center for Life Science will start clinical
trials in October on two traditional Chinese medicines for
cardiovascular diseases, said Kuebler.
</P>
<P>
He said, "I believe that there is a curiosity in the United
States about traditional Chinese medicine. And there is a very
large market place in the United States for products which are
based on botanical plants." 
</P>
</TEXT>
