<HEADLINE> British Insurance Company Opens Branch in Cuba </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HAVANA, October 3 (Xinhua) -- The Heath British Group, one of
the world's leading insurance company, has opened here an office,
the first foreign insurance brokerage authorized by the Cuban
authorities.
</P>
<P>
The office is a joint venture of Heath Overseas Broking, of the
Heath British group, which owns 49 percent of the stock, and the
Empresa de Seguros Internacionales de Cuba (ESICUBA), which
controls 51 percent, said Alejandro Gil, manager of the new entity.
</P>
<P>
"Know-how is one of the foreign partner's fundamental
contributions, while ESICUBA's is the knowledge of the Cuban
insurance market," added Alejandro Gil.
</P>
<P>
The Heath Group, established in 1877, has more than 80 branches
all over the world, and is the strongest of its kind in Latin
America, said a Cuban official on Saturday.
</P>
<P>
Cuba has three state-owned insurance companies: ESICUBA, La
Isla and ESEN, specialized in several fields. 
</P>
</TEXT>
