<HEADLINE> 27 Kg Ecstasy Materials Confiscated in Jakarta </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JAKARTA, October 4 (Xinhua) -- A total of 27 kilograms of
ecstasy materials and several thousand pieces of ecstasy were
confiscated by the Jakarta police during a pre-dawn raid Saturday,
Antara News Agency reported Sunday.
</P>
<P>
The police detained three people for allegedly producing and
trafficking in the drug, head of the police detective unit Col.
Gories Mere said.
</P>
<P>
The security officers also arrested two girls for allegedly
molding the drug.
</P>
<P>
"The success is inseparable from the hard work of our men who
continued spying on suspected places for a whole month," said
Gories who led the raid.
</P>
<P>
The raid followed a tip that ecstasy trafficker Agung Siswanto
who hails from Central Java was about to make an ecstasy deal. The
police arrested Siswanto Friday night and seized 1,660 pieces of
ecstasy from him.
</P>
<P>
Siswanto said he bought the psychotropics from Erwin who had an
ecstasy producing plant in North Jakarta. The police then clamped
down on the plant and confiscated 2,867 pieces of ecstasy and 27
kilograms of materials used in the production of the dangerous
drug. 
</P>
</TEXT>
