<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Villa Extends Lead, Man United Move to Second </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LONDON, October 3 (Xinhua) -- Two goals from midfielder Ian
Taylor gave Aston Villa a 2-1 victory at Coventry at the English
Premier League on Saturday.
</P>
<P>
With the win, Aston Villa extended its leading place by six
points in the team standings.
</P>
<P>
Taylor scored Villa's goals after 29 and 39 minutes, with
Trond Egil Soltvedt (71) replying for Coventry. Villa now have 20
points from eight games.
</P>
<P>
Manchester United, who have played a game less than Villa,
moved into second spot on 14 points thanks to a 3-0 win at bottom
club Southampton. Dwight Yorke (11), Andy Cole (59) and Dutchman
Jordi Cruyff (74) scored United's goals.
</P>
<P>
New Tottenham Hotspur manager George Graham watched from the
stands as his new club won 1-0 at Derby County, England defender
Sol Campbell scoring the only goal on the hour.
</P>
<P>
Danish striker Mikkel Beck netted twice in Middlesbrough's 4-0
home win over Sheffield Wednesday and there were also wins for
Blackburn Rovers, Everton, Charlton and Leicester, who beat
Graham's old club Leeds United 1-0.
</P>
<P>
On Sunday champions Arsenal play host to Newcastle United and
Liverpool take on Chelsea at Anfield. 
</P>
