<HEADLINE> Beijingers Opt for National Day Weddings </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, October 4 (Xinhua) -- An ever increasing number of
Chinese couples are opting to exchange wedding vows on October 1,
China's National Day.
</P>
<P>
Photo shops in downtown Beijing opened for business early on
National Day, with brides arriving early for photo sessions and
then scurrying home to meet their bridegrooms.
</P>
<P>
Car rental agencies and taxi companies enjoyed brisk business,
and the Shuxin Wedding Consultants arranged five weddings on
October 1, or the National Day.
</P>
<P>
Sun Tao, a bridegroom from south Beijing, decorated a rented
Lincoln Continental with three giant flower baskets containing
16 dozen roses which he purchased at 10 times the normal price.
</P>
<P>
Fancy limousines are far cry from the bridal sedan chairs used
throughout China in ancient times. Young Beijingers prefer
Cadillac, Lincoln or Mercedes-Benz sedans which rent for as much
as 5,000 yuan (600 U.S. dollars) for half a day. Some even opt
for a Rolls-Royce.
</P>
<P>
High rental fees for limousines fail to deter young people from
having a stylish wedding.  
</P>
</TEXT>
