<TEXT>
<P>
AMMAN -- Hundreds of foreign workers, mainly Asians, have been
arrested in a bid to return job chances to unemployed Jordanians,
local paper said Saturday.
</P>
<P>
"The aim of this campaign is to put an end to those who are
working illegally in the country" and it is also part of the
government's drive to combat the problem of unemployment of the
Jordanians, Minister of Interior Nayef Al Qadi late Friday told
the semi-official Jordan Times.
</P>
<P>
Through this campaign, the government can check the working
status of these workers and ensure that the relevant laws are not
violated, he added. (Jordan-Arrest-Guest Workers)
