<HEADLINE> UN Investigates Its Mission in Cyprus </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
UNITED NATIONS, October 3 (Xinhua) -- The United Nations was
investigating its mission in Cyprus for possible abuses over
access to duty-free liquor and cigarettes, U.N. spokesman's office
announced on Saturday.
</P>
<P>
The spokesman's office said the possible abuse by a small
number of members of the United Nations Peace keeping Force in
Cyprus (UNFICYP) was discovered by a routine UNFICYP check and an
investigation immediately began.
</P>
<P>
It said a formal report was expected to be sent to U.N.
Headquarters in New York and necessary action would be taken in
accordance with U.N. rules after the investigation was completed.
</P>
<P>
UNFICYP, which was established in 1964, is aimed at monitoring
the ceasefire between the Turkish Cypriots in the north of the
island and the Greek Cypriots in the south.  
</P>
